fields.Name: AES-256-GCM
fields.Description: AES 256-bit encryption with Galois/Counter Mode. Provides authenticated encryption (AEAD) which detects tampering. RECOMMENDED for most use cases. Requires 32-byte key (openssl rand -base64 32).

fields.Name: AES-256-CBC
fields.Description: AES 256-bit encryption with Cipher Block Chaining. Does NOT provide authentication - use AES-256-GCM instead for new implementations. Requires 32-byte key.

fields.Name: AES-128-GCM
fields.Description: AES 128-bit encryption with Galois/Counter Mode. Provides authenticated encryption (AEAD). Requires 16-byte key (openssl rand -base64 16). Use AES-256-GCM for higher security.
